    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="1391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.34112 RP/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Conversations with Paraguayan officials regarding forced sale or intervention
                    of local firms on the Proclaimed List have recently progressed favorably and it
                    apparently may be possible to arrange for the creation of a Paraguayan authority
                    which will supervise the sale and transfer of the more important German
                    interests to acceptable Paraguayan firms or individuals. The problem of finance
                    appears to be most conspicuous and inquiry has been made of me by Finance and
                    Foreign Affairs Ministers<note n="53" xml:id="d1391fn53">Rogelio Espinoza and
                        Luis A. Argaña, respectively.</note> as to possibility of Paraguayan
                    Government securing such aid from the American Government. Department’s circular
                    instruction December 17, 1942<note n="54" xml:id="d1391fn54">Not printed.</note>
                    regarding the forced sale and intervention of Proclaimed List business
                    enterprises indicates that under proper circumstances such funds might be
                    available from Export-Import Bank.</p>
                <p>Possibility seems to exist of encouraging forced sale of such firms as German
                    bank, Staudt, Krauch, Ferreterías Universal and Alemana, Tubos, Mannes, Mann and
                    Wiske, the leading German firms in Asunción. Total assets probably do not exceed
                    $1,500,000. However, before continuing these conversations Paraguayan Ministers
                    wish to confirm whether in principle if forced sale of these firms to
                    Paraguayans is provided by decree law the funds required might be made available
                    by the Export-Import Bank to finance such transfers through whatever government
                    organization may be set up by Paraguay to supervise such transactions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
